          "body": "At the chronological center of the chapter, when 'all hope of our being saved was gradually abandoned' (27:20), an angel stands beside Paul with a four-part word: *do not be afraid*; *you must stand before Caesar*; *God has granted you* (*kecharistai*, perfect tense — already given as a completed gift) *all those sailing with you*. The vision recapitulates 23:11 and grounds everything that follows. Paul does not bargain for the lives on board; God *bestows* them on him. This is intercessory providence — the wicked sail safely because a righteous man is on board (echoing Genesis 18:23-32; the same pattern by which Joseph's house was blessed for Joseph's sake, Genesis 39:5)."
