          "title": "The 276 souls and the value Luke places on each",
          "body": "Luke pauses at 27:37 to record an exact number: *we were two hundred and seventy-six persons*. He does not need to. He does so because the angelic promise was that God had granted Paul *all* those sailing with him (27:24), and Luke is counting the receipts. Every soul matters — soldiers who would have killed Paul (27:42), sailors who tried to abandon ship (27:30), prisoners on their way to execution in Rome, passengers, the centurion. All 276 reach land. Paul's promise at 27:34 — *not a hair from the head of any of you will perish* — echoes Jesus' words in Luke 12:7 and 21:18, and is fulfilled to the syllable at 27:44: *they all were brought safely to land*."
